20/09/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Bulgaria and Britain have signed a protocol on the exchange of confidential information regarding organised crime, according to the latest edition of the Bulgarian State Gazette. 
Interior Minister Georgi Petkanov and British Ambassador to Sofia Jeremy Hill signed the agreement, which provides for enhanced co-operation in fighting terrorism, drug trafficking and illegal migration, corruption and money laundering.
In related news, Sofia hosts an international conference Monday on preventing money laundering. 
Representatives of financial police and investigative services from 15 European countries are attending.
Parliament, meanwhile, has approved the deployment of military doctors to Afghanistan next month. 
They will stay for six months, joining NATO's multinational contingent at a new military hospital in Kabul. 
(Sega, Dnevnik, bTV, BNT - 20/09/04)
